  <!-- Full details by SKU: lead paragraph(s) shown, the rest in accordions. -->
  <template data-pdp="MTW-FV-PNK">
    <div class="pdp__lead"><p>A hand-felted pink blossom cottage — the signature piece of our Fairy Villages line. The pointed roof is built of overlapping wool petals stitched one at a time; the doorway opens onto a hollow interior where a small fairy or gnome can live, sit, or sleep.</p></div>
    <details class="acc" open><summary>About this piece</summary><div class="acc__body"><p>Every house is hand-stitched in Nepal by a women's felting cooperative. Wool is sourced from Australia and New Zealand, hand-rolled and shaped without molds — meaning no two houses are identical. Tiny differences in petal angle and curve mark each one as the work of a particular maker.</p></div></details>
    <details class="acc"><summary>Educator notes</summary><div class="acc__body"><p>The anchor piece for spring nature tables, small-world play, and the Fairy Villages classroom set. Pairs naturally with Wonderheart wooden gnomes (4″ or mini) — the open doorway is sized to receive both.</p></div></details>
    <details class="acc"><summary>Specifications</summary><div class="acc__body"><ul><li>Hand-stitched wool felt over an internal armature</li><li>Approximately 7″ tall</li><li>Spot-clean only · fair-trade · handmade in Nepal</li><li>Ages 3–8</li></ul></div></details>
  </template>
  <template data-pdp="MTW-FV-LIL">
    <div class="pdp__lead"><p>A hand-felted lilac blossom cottage — the dusk-toned sibling of the Pink Blossom House. The roof of curled wool petals reads as lilac at one angle and pale violet at another; the doorway opens onto a hollow interior big enough to seat a small fairy or wooden gnome.</p></div>
    <details class="acc" open><summary>About this piece</summary><div class="acc__body"><p>Hand-stitched in Nepal by a women's felting cooperative. Wool is sourced from Australia and New Zealand and felted by hand without molds, so no two houses are identical — petal angles, curve depths, and color saturation all carry the maker's fingerprint.</p></div></details>
    <details class="acc"><summary>Educator notes</summary><div class="acc__body"><p>A favorite for spring–early summer nature tables. Pairs with the Wonderheart Mini Pastel Purple or Pink Gnome for the most natural color story.</p></div></details>
    <details class="acc"><summary>Specifications</summary><div class="acc__body"><ul><li>Hand-stitched wool felt over an internal armature</li><li>Approximately 7″ tall</li><li>Spot-clean only · fair-trade · handmade in Nepal</li><li>Ages 3–8</li></ul></div></details>
  </template>
  <template data-pdp="MTW-FV-RBN">
    <div class="pdp__lead"><p>A large hand-felted shimmer home in rainbow tones, fixed to a round felt base. The door opens and closes; the cone roof rises high enough to receive a small fairy, gnome, or doll inside. The hero piece for a rainbow-themed nature shelf.</p></div>
    <details class="acc" open><summary>Developmental benefits</summary><div class="acc__body"><ul><li>Large-scale fairy home supports sustained small-world play and multi-child rotation</li><li>Working door (opens/closes) develops fine motor and supports threshold-story play</li><li>Rainbow palette invites color-sorting and pattern-matching with felt loose parts</li><li>Open-ended interior receives any small figures — fairies, gnomes, dolls, peg people</li><li>Heirloom hand-felted craftsmanship from a women's cooperative — fair-trade made</li></ul></div></details>
    <details class="acc"><summary>Learning connections</summary><div class="acc__body"><p>Small-World Play · Narrative Play · Fairy &amp; Gnome Play · Color Recognition · Fine Motor (door) · Sensory Exploration.</p></div></details>
    <details class="acc"><summary>Classroom specifications</summary><div class="acc__body"><ul><li><strong>Maker:</strong> Himalayan Felt Co.</li><li><strong>Material:</strong> 100% sheep's wool sourced from Australia &amp; New Zealand</li><li><strong>Dimensions:</strong> 12.59″ base diameter · 16.5″ total height</li><li><strong>Safety &amp; compliance:</strong> CE-certified · European toy standard · child-safe non-toxic dyes</li><li><strong>Origin:</strong> Hand-felted in Nepal by a women's cooperative under Fair Trade</li><li><strong>Ages:</strong> 3–8 · Note: roof does not detach; house attached to base</li></ul></div></details>
    <details class="acc"><summary>Pairs with</summary><div class="acc__body"><p>Wonderheart Pastel Gnomes · Bumbu Flower Children · Papoose Fairy Door · felt loose parts.</p></div></details>
  </template>
  <template data-pdp="MTW-FV-RBS">
    <div class="pdp__lead"><p>A hand-felted fairy house with a cone roof and stitched-flower detailing, anchored to a round wool-felt mat. The door opens and closes onto a hollow interior ready for fairies, gnomes, or dolls. Colors range across the rainbow spectrum.</p></div>
    <details class="acc" open><summary>Developmental benefits</summary><div class="acc__body"><ul><li>House + mat as a single ready-to-play landscape — no setup required</li><li>Working door (opens/closes) develops fine motor and supports threshold-story play</li><li>Rainbow palette invites color-sorting and pattern-matching with felt loose parts</li><li>Round mat anchors the play space without overwhelming the table</li></ul></div></details>
